C++17 Console Music Player
    A simple console-based music player written in C++17 using SFML Audio and standard filesystem.

Features
    Plays .wav files from a specified music directory

Commands:

    p — Pause
    r — Resume
    s — Stop
    n — Next track
    q — Quit player

Usage
    Place .wav files in the ../music directory (relative to executable).

Build with C++17 and SFML.
Run the executable and control playback via keyboard commands.

------------------------------------------
Build and Run player:
Note: need gcc-11

Set kit or Toolchain

1.  Preferred
    
    Press Ctrl+Shift+P → CMake: Select a Kit
    select /home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin/g++-11

2.
    $mkdir build
    $cd build

    $cmake -DCMAKE_C_COMPILER=/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin/gcc-11 -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER=/home/linuxbrew/.linuxbrew/bin/g++-11 ..
    $make

    $./sfml-app
------------------------------------------
Ref:
The Missing Package Manager for macOS (or Linux)
https://brew.sh/